column4:
@KosmosEnergy has reached an agreement with the #Senegalese government to relinquish its 90% equity stake in the Yakaar-Teranga #gas field #development to @Groupe_PETROSEN, giving the state-owned entity full ownership of the asset. The agreement includes no financial compensation to Kosmos Energy as the license was due to expire by July 2026. 

The withdrawal comes after BP's exit in 2023 largely as a result of disagreements towards a gas development strategy. The multinationals preferred exports while the Senegalese government opted for domestic utilization. The asset is one of Senegal's largest gas discoveries with an estimated recoverable reserves of 25 trillion cubic feet.

For more up-to-date market intelligence in #Africa's energy industry, visit https://t.co/MLdMCx15PB

